# Python command example requirement

When creating or editing any `.py` file, include a short module docstring at the top with an executable command example.

Requirements:
- Put the example at the top of the file in the opening docstring.
- Use a repo-root runnable command (typically `python3 path/to/file.py ...`).
- Keep the example aligned with the file's actual CLI flags and behavior.
- If a file has no CLI entrypoint, add a brief note in the docstring explaining how to run the relevant function/module instead.
